Vice President Kamala Harris spoke at the Sheraton Philadelphia Downtown, praising the work of Pennsylvania Democrats in the 2022 elections. She highlighted the victories Democrats achieved, such as defeating big lies and extremism in secretary of state races and defending reproductive rights in several states. Harris emphasized the momentum Democrats have and the need to continue delivering on their promises. She also criticized extremist leaders who seek to divide the nation and called on Democrats to unify the country. Harris listed the values and rights the Democratic Party stands for, including marriage equality, gun control, reproductive rights, and equality for all races, genders, and religions. She then introduced President Joe Biden, praising him for his clarity on his values and the people he fights for.